Call for Papers
Purdue Linguistics Association Working Papers
Vol. 1, Issue 2

Submission Deadline: June 6, 2008 @ 5pm

We are looking for papers in any area related to linguistics, including,
but not limited to:
-	Phonetics
-	Phonology
-	Syntax
-	Semantics
-	Sociolinguistics
-	Psycholinguistics
-	Historical Linguistics
-	Anthropological Linguistics
-	Computational Linguistics
-	First Language Acquisition
-	Second Language Acquisition
-	Second Language Writing
-	Speech and Hearing Sciences

Formatting Guidelines
-	Word document format (.doc)
-	12 point font, double spaced, Times New Roman
-	Include a cover sheet with the following information:
-	Name as it will appear in the publication
-	Affiliation
-	Email address
-	The length should not exceed 30 pages including references, tables,
figures, appendices, etc.
-	Tables, Figures, Graphs, etc. should be sent as a separate file as image
files (.jpg) 
-	Footnotes/Endnotes should be at the end of the paper.  Please do NOT
embed them into the text using Microsoft Word auto-formatting.  
-	As this will be an anonymous review, please do not refer to your previous
publications in first person.
-	References should follow the guidelines set by APA
-	Please see Purdue's OWL site for help with APA guidelines:
http://owl.english.purdue.edu/owl/resource/560/01/

Review Process
-	Double blind review
-	Your paper will be read by at least two reviewers for content, quality,
and relevance 

Please send your paper (cover sheet + 30 pages, including images) to Carly
Houston (ckhousto@purdue.edu) by June 6, 2008 @ 5pm EST.  Papers submitted
past the deadline will not be accepted.  You will be notified of your
acceptance by no later than July 4.

Thank you, and please feel free to contact us if you have any questions. 

Purdue Linguistics Association 



Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics







